---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<Base title="How Raft Works" description="Leader election, log replication, and safety in the Raft consensus algorithm, with interactive SVG animations.">

  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 pt-16 pb-8">
    <p class="text-sky-400 text-sm font-mono mb-3">Chapter 2</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">How Raft Works</h1>
    <p class="text-slate-400 text-lg mb-6">
      Raft decomposes consensus into three sub-problems: leader election,
      log replication, and safety. Each is understandable in isolation.
    </p>
    <div class="flex gap-3 text-sm flex-wrap">
      <a href="#leader-election" class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-800 hover:bg-slate-700 text-slate-300 rounded-lg transition">Leader Election</a>
      <a href="#log-replication" class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-800 hover:bg-slate-700 text-slate-300 rounded-lg transition">Log Replication</a>
      <a href="#safety" class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-800 hover:bg-slate-700 text-slate-300 rounded-lg transition">Safety</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Core insight -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-4">
    <div class="bg-sky-900/20 border border-sky-700/40 rounded-xl p-5">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-sky-400 mb-2">Core insight: strong leader</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Raft uses a <strong class="text-slate-200">strong leader model</strong>. One node is the
        authoritative leader at all times. All writes go through the leader.
        This simplifies design enormously — consistency flows from having a single source of truth.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Server states -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Server states</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-yellow-700/50 p-5">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-yellow-500/20 border-2 border-yellow-500 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-mono font-bold text-yellow-400 mb-3">L</div>
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-yellow-400 mb-1">Leader</h4>
        <p class="text-slate-400 text-xs leading-relaxed">Handles all client requests. Replicates log entries to followers. Sends heartbeats to prevent new elections.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-indigo-700/50 p-5">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-indigo-500/20 border-2 border-indigo-500 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-mono font-bold text-indigo-400 mb-3">F</div>
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-indigo-400 mb-1">Follower</h4>
        <p class="text-slate-400 text-xs leading-relaxed">Passive. Responds to leaders and candidates. Becomes a candidate if it hears nothing within the election timeout.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-emerald-700/50 p-5">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-emerald-500/20 border-2 border-emerald-500 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-mono font-bold text-emerald-400 mb-3">C</div>
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-emerald-400 mb-1">Candidate</h4>
        <p class="text-slate-400 text-xs leading-relaxed">Trying to become leader. Requests votes from other nodes. Becomes leader if it wins a majority.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Terms -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Terms: logical time</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Raft divides time into <strong class="text-slate-200">terms</strong> — monotonically increasing integers.
      Each term begins with an election. If nobody wins (split vote), a new term begins immediately.
      Nodes with a stale term immediately revert to follower.
    </p>
    <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-slate-700 p-5 font-mono text-sm overflow-x-auto">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 500 60" class="w-full" style="height:60px">
        <rect x="0"   y="10" width="130" height="30" rx="4" fill="#4f46e5" opacity="0.7"/>
        <text x="65"  y="30" text-anchor="middle" fill="white" font-size="11" font-family="monospace">Term 1 — Leader: N1</text>
        <rect x="134" y="10" width="50"  height="30" rx="4" fill="#7f1d1d" opacity="0.7"/>
        <text x="159" y="30" text-anchor="middle" fill="#fca5a5" font-size="10" font-family="monospace">T2 split</text>
        <rect x="188" y="10" width="150" height="30" rx="4" fill="#4f46e5" opacity="0.7"/>
        <text x="263" y="30" text-anchor="middle" fill="white" font-size="11" font-family="monospace">Term 3 — Leader: N3</text>
        <rect x="342" y="10" width="110" height="30" rx="4" fill="#4f46e5" opacity="0.7"/>
        <text x="397" y="30" text-anchor="middle" fill="white" font-size="11" font-family="monospace">Term 4 — N2</text>
        <text x="460" y="32" fill="#475569" font-size="10" font-family="monospace">→ time</text>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Leader election -->
  <section id="leader-election" class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
      <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-emerald-900/40 text-emerald-400 text-xs font-mono rounded">Phase 1</span>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Leader Election</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-8 text-slate-400 leading-relaxed text-sm">
      <p><strong class="text-slate-200">1. Heartbeat timeout.</strong> Each follower has an election timeout (randomized, 150–300ms). No heartbeat → starts an election.</p>
      <p><strong class="text-slate-200">2. Become candidate.</strong> Increments its term, votes for itself, sends <code class="text-sky-300 bg-slate-800 px-1 rounded">RequestVote</code> to all peers.</p>
      <p><strong class="text-slate-200">3. Vote rules.</strong> A node grants its vote if: (a) hasn't voted in this term, and (b) candidate's log is at least as up-to-date.</p>
      <p><strong class="text-slate-200">4. Win majority.</strong> ⌊n/2⌋ + 1 votes → becomes leader, sends heartbeats immediately.</p>
      <p><strong class="text-slate-200">5. Randomized timeouts</strong> prevent split votes — two nodes rarely start elections at the exact same millisecond.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Election SVG demo -->
    <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-2xl border border-slate-700 p-6 flex flex-col gap-4" data-cluster-root>
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-white text-sm">Interactive: Leader Election</h3>
        <div class="flex gap-2">
          <button data-cluster="election" data-action="election"
            class="px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-mono bg-emerald-900/50 hover:bg-emerald-800/60 text-emerald-300 rounded-lg border border-emerald-700/40 transition">
            Run Election
          </button>
          <button data-cluster="election" data-action="kill"
            class="px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-mono bg-red-900/50 hover:bg-red-800/60 text-red-300 rounded-lg border border-red-700/40 transition">
            Kill Leader
          </button>
          <button data-cluster="election" data-action="reset"
            class="px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-mono bg-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-600 text-slate-300 rounded-lg transition">
            Reset
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <svg id="svg-election" viewBox="0 0 600 280" class="w-full" style="height:280px"
           data-cluster="election" data-node-count="5">
        <g id="edges-election"></g>
        <g id="nodes-election"></g>
        <g id="packets-election"></g>
      </svg>
      <div id="log-election"
        class="font-mono text-xs text-slate-400 space-y-0.5 min-h-[48px] max-h-[80px] overflow-y-auto leading-5">
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Log replication -->
  <section id="log-replication" class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
      <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-sky-900/40 text-sky-400 text-xs font-mono rounded">Phase 2</span>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Log Replication</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-8 text-slate-400 leading-relaxed text-sm">
      <p><strong class="text-slate-200">The replicated log.</strong> Each Raft node keeps an ordered log of commands. The goal is identical logs across all nodes.</p>
      <p><strong class="text-slate-200">1. Client → leader.</strong> Client sends a command (e.g. <code class="text-sky-300 bg-slate-800 px-1 rounded">SET x=5</code>). Followers redirect to the leader.</p>
      <p><strong class="text-slate-200">2. Append entry.</strong> Leader appends it to its log with the current term number.</p>
      <p><strong class="text-slate-200">3. AppendEntries RPCs.</strong> Leader sends the new entry to all followers in parallel.</p>
      <p><strong class="text-slate-200">4. Commit on majority.</strong> Once a majority ACKs, the leader marks it committed and applies it to its state machine.</p>
      <p><strong class="text-slate-200">5. Consistency check.</strong> Each <code class="text-sky-300 bg-slate-800 px-1 rounded">AppendEntries</code> includes the previous entry's index + term. Mismatches are rejected — logs never diverge.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Log replication SVG demo -->
    <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-2xl border border-slate-700 p-6 flex flex-col gap-4" data-cluster-root>
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-white text-sm">Interactive: Log Replication</h3>
        <div class="flex gap-2">
          <button data-cluster="replication" data-action="election"
            class="px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-mono bg-emerald-900/50 hover:bg-emerald-800/60 text-emerald-300 rounded-lg border border-emerald-700/40 transition">
            Elect Leader
          </button>
          <button data-cluster="replication" data-action="send"
            class="px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-mono bg-sky-900/50 hover:bg-sky-800/60 text-sky-300 rounded-lg border border-sky-700/40 transition">
            Send Command
          </button>
          <button data-cluster="replication" data-action="reset"
            class="px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-mono bg-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-600 text-slate-300 rounded-lg transition">
            Reset
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <svg id="svg-replication" viewBox="0 0 600 280" class="w-full" style="height:280px"
           data-cluster="replication" data-node-count="5">
        <g id="edges-replication"></g>
        <g id="nodes-replication"></g>
        <g id="packets-replication"></g>
      </svg>
      <div id="log-replication-log"
        class="font-mono text-xs text-slate-400 space-y-0.5 min-h-[48px] max-h-[80px] overflow-y-auto leading-5">
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Note: log div id conflict workaround -->
    <script>
      // The section id="log-replication" conflicts with the log div id,
      // so we renamed the log div to "log-replication-log" and alias it here.
      document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
        const alias = document.getElementById('log-replication-log');
        if (alias) alias.id = 'log-replication';
      });
    </script>
  </section>

  <!-- Safety -->
  <section id="safety" class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
      <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-red-900/40 text-red-400 text-xs font-mono rounded">Phase 3</span>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Safety Guarantees</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
      {[
        ['Election Safety', 'At most one leader per term. Two majorities always share at least one node, which can only vote once per term.'],
        ['Leader Append-Only', 'A leader never overwrites its log — only appends. Committed entries are permanent.'],
        ['Log Matching', 'If two logs share an entry at the same index + term, all preceding entries are identical. Enforced inductively by the consistency check.'],
        ['Leader Completeness', 'A leader always has all committed entries. The vote rule (log up-to-date check) ensures nodes that missed committed entries can never win.'],
        ['State Machine Safety', 'No two nodes ever apply different commands at the same log index. This is the top-level correctness guarantee.'],
      ].map(([title, desc]) => (
        <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-slate-700 p-5">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-white mb-1">{title}</h4>
          <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">{desc}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-700/40 rounded-xl p-5">
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-400 mb-2">What Raft does NOT guarantee</h4>
      <ul class="text-slate-400 text-sm space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>No progress if majority of nodes are unreachable (CP, not AP — by design)</li>
        <li>No protection against Byzantine faults (lying/corrupting nodes)</li>
        <li>No low latency guarantee — a write needs at least 2 round-trips</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
      <a href={`${base}/problem`} class="px-4 py-2 bg-slate-800 hover:bg-slate-700 text-slate-300 rounded-lg transition text-sm">← The Problem</a>
      <a href={`${base}/in-the-wild`} class="px-6 py-3 bg-sky-600 hover:bg-sky-500 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg transition">Next: In the Wild →</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<script>
  import { initClusters } from '../scripts/raft-cluster';
  initClusters();
</script>
